Definition: a congenital disease affecting T cells that can result from a mutation in any one of several different genes
Example: children with it are susceptible to infectious disease; if untreated it is lethal within the first year or two of life
Synonyms: severe_combined_immunodeficiency_disease, SCID, immunodeficiency, monogenic_disorder, a, congenital, disease, affecting, T, cells, that, can, result, from, mutation, in, any, one, of, several, different, genes, children, with, it, are, susceptible, to, infectious, if, untreated, is, lethal, within, the, first, year, or, two, life
Category: noun.state
